69649.name: Abusive Sergeant
69649.text: Battlecry: Give a minion +2 Attack this turn.
69649.flavorText: ADD ME TO YOUR DECK, MAGGOT!

111318.name: Acolyte of Death
111318.text: After a friendly Undead dies, draw a card.
111318.flavorText: "I see dead people. A LOT of dead people."

76316.name: Acolyte of Pain
76316.text: Whenever this minion takes damage, draw a card.
76316.flavorText: He trained when he was younger to be an acolyte of joy, but things didn’t work out like he thought they would.

69632.name: Al'Akir the Windlord
69632.flavorText: He is the weakest of the four Elemental Lords. And the other three don't let him forget it.

69507.name: Aldrachi Warblades
69507.flavorText: The ancient Aldrachi were the greatest warriors in the universe. Imagine their power if they'd put the handle at the END of the blade.

111467.name: Alexstrasza
111467.text: Battlecry: Set a hero's remaining Health to 15.
111467.flavorText: Alexstrasza the Life-Binder brings life and hope to everyone. Except Deathwing. And Malygos. And Nekros.

76291.name: Ancient of Lore
76291.text: Choose One - Draw 2 cards; or Restore 7 Health.
76291.flavorText: Go ahead, carve your initials in him.

76297.name: Animal Companion
76297.flavorText: You could summon Misha, Leokk, or Huffer! Huffer is more trouble than he's worth.

69718.name: Annoy-o-Tron
69718.flavorText: The inventor of the Annoy-o-Tron was immediately expelled from Tinkerschool, Tinkertown, and was eventually exiled from the Eastern Kingdoms altogether.

78342.name: Anti-Magic Shell
78342.flavorText: Using a spell to counter magic - a bit hypocritical don't you think?

97374.name: Arcane Artificer
97374.text: Whenever you cast a spell, gain Armor equal to its Cost.
97374.flavorText: Ethereal armor dissipates in 6 hours which can cause extreme awkwardness for first time buyers.

69500.name: Arcane Intellect
69500.flavorText: Playing this card makes you SMARTER. And let's face it: we could all stand to be a little smarter.

69546.name: Arcane Shot
69546.flavorText: Magi conjured arcane arrows to sell to hunters, until hunters learned just enough magic to do it themselves. The resulting loss of jobs sent Stormwind into a minor recession.

69702.name: Arcanologist
69702.flavorText: What did you draw? Shhhh… it’s a secret.

111455.name: Arch-Villain Rafaam
111455.text: Taunt Battlecry: Replace your hand and deck with Legendary minions.
111455.flavorText: Minions must wash hands before being LIQUIDATED AND REPLACED BY SOMEONE BETTER.

69611.name: Argent Protector
69611.flavorText: "I'm not saying you can dodge fireballs. I'm saying with this shield, you won't have to."

102223.name: Armor Vendor
102223.flavorText: "You look like the kind of person that would buy three sets of armor. One to wear, a spare, and a spare for the spare."

78352.name: Army of the Dead
78352.text: Raise up to 5 Corpses as 2/2 Risen Ghouls with Rush.

111317.name: Asphyxiate
111317.text: Destroy the highest Attack enemy minion.
111317.flavorText: I find your abundance of Attack disturbing.

69525.name: Assassinate
69525.flavorText: If you don't want to be assassinated, move to the Barrens and change your name. Good luck!

69700.name: Babbling Book
69700.text: Battlecry: Add a random Mage spell to your hand.
69700.flavorText: His idol is the Green Hills of Stranglethorn, and he won't shut up about it.

69521.name: Backstab
69521.text: Deal 2 damage to an undamaged minion.
69521.flavorText: It's funny how often yelling "Look over there!" gets your opponent to turn around.

111364.name: Ball of Spiders
111364.text: Summon three 1/1 Webspinners with "Deathrattle: Get a random Beast."

111357.name: Barak Kodobane
111357.flavorText: They say he's a pro at horseback archery.

69674.name: Baron Geddon
69674.text: At the end of your turn, deal 2 damage to ALL other characters.
69674.flavorText: Baron Geddon was Ragnaros's foremost lieutenant, until he got FIRED.

76304.name: Bash
76304.flavorText: You might think bashing doesn't take a lot of practice. It doesn't.

78353.name: Battlefield Necromancer
78353.text: At the end of your turn, raise a Corpse as a 1/3 Risen Footman with Taunt.
78353.flavorText: Coming soon: the Hand Necromancer and the Deck Necromancer.

69586.name: Battlefiend
69586.text: After your hero attacks, gain +1 Attack.
69586.flavorText: Say what you like about my hatchet-headed hooligan, he’s my battle-friend.

76318.name: Beaming Sidekick
76318.flavorText: Sure, I'll carry the water! And the food! And the tents! And the cursed monkey paw!

69652.name: Big Game Hunter
69652.text: Tradeable Battlecry: Destroy a minion with 7 or more Attack.
69652.flavorText: Mere devilsaurs no longer excite him. Soon he'll be trying to catch Onyxia with only a dull Krol Blade.

97332.name: Bladestorm
97332.text: Deal 1 damage to all minions. Repeat until one dies.
97332.flavorText: Dear minions: Woosh, woosh, woosh, woosh, woosh. Best regards, Bladestorm

76273.name: Blizzard
76273.text: Deal 2 damage to all enemy minions and Freeze them.
76273.flavorText: This spell can be very Entertaining.

111321.name: Blood Tap
111321.text: Give all minions in your hand +1/+1. Spend 2 Corpses to give them +1/+1 more.
111321.flavorText: Come join us in the tavern! We have whatever you're drinking on tap. Yes, even that.

113309.name: Bloodbound Imp
113309.text: Whenever this attacks, deal 2 damage to your hero.
113309.flavorText: ALWAYS read the terms and conditions.

69655.name: Bloodmage Thalnos
69655.flavorText: He's in charge of the Annual Scarlet Monastery Blood Drive!

69677.name: Bloodsail Raider
69677.text: Battlecry: Gain Attack equal to the Attack of your weapon.
69677.flavorText: "I only plunder on days that end in 'y'."

112924.name: Boulderfist Ogre
112924.flavorText: "ME HAVE GOOD STATS FOR THE COST"

69640.name: Brawl
69640.text: Destroy all minions except one. (chosen randomly)
69640.flavorText: Do you know the first rule of Brawl Club?

86545.name: Bronze Explorer
86545.flavorText: Always ready to explore new friendships! Except with Deathwing.

102219.name: Bronze Gatekeeper
102219.flavorText: "You have my shield! And the rest of me too."

113117.name: Cargo Guard
113117.text: At the end of your turn, gain 3 Armor.

102199.name: Catrina Muerte
102199.text: At the end of your turn, resurrect another friendly Undead minion.
102199.flavorText: She always manages to lift your spirits.

69598.name: Cenarius
69598.text: Choose One - Give your other minions +2/+2; or Summon two 2/2 Treants with Taunt.
69598.flavorText: Yes, he's a demigod. No, he doesn't need to wear a shirt.

69558.name: Chaos Strike
69558.text: Give your hero +2 Attack this turn. Draw a card.
69558.flavorText: "What do we want?" "CHAOS!" "When do we want it?" "WHEN LEAST EXPECTED!"

80647.name: Chillfallen Baron
80647.flavorText: He hates when people call 60 degree weather cold.

69666.name: Coldlight Seer
69666.flavorText: The Coldlight murlocs reside in the darkest pits of the Abyssal Depths. So no, there's no getting away from murlocs.

69532.name: Consecration
69532.flavorText: Consecrated ground glows with Holy energy. But it smells a little, too.

69504.name: Coordinated Strike
69504.flavorText: Undisputed champions of "Dancing with the Satyrs."

111315.name: Corpse Bride
111315.text: Battlecry: Spend up to 10 Corpses to summon a Risen Groom with Taunt and that much Attack and Health.

111334.name: Corpse Explosion
111334.text: Detonate a Corpse to deal 1 damage to all minions. If any are still alive, repeat this.
111334.flavorText: What? It's not like they were using them anymore.

69607.name: Counterspell
69607.text: Secret: When your opponent casts a spell, Counter it.
69607.flavorText: What's the difference between a mage playing with Counterspell and a mage who isn't? The mage who isn't is getting Pyroblasted in the face.

69661.name: Crazed Alchemist
69661.text: Battlecry: Swap the Attack and Health of a minion.
69661.flavorText: "You'll love my new recipe!" he says... especially if you're not happy with your current number of limbs.

69683.name: Crimson Sigil Runner
69683.flavorText: He's not the fastest of the bunch, but he'll take a stab at it anyway.

96917.name: Crusader Aura
96917.text: Whenever a friendly minion attacks, give it +2/+1. Lasts turns.

102224.name: Cult Neophyte
102224.text: Battlecry: Your opponent's spells cost (1) more next turn.
102224.flavorText: Make a new recruit's deficiencies your efficiencies.

111454.name: Dark Alley Pact
111454.text: Summon a Fiend with Taunt and stats equal to your hand size.
111454.flavorText: "With your help, I can finally install some proper lighting in this alley."

69522.name: Deadly Poison
69522.flavorText: Rogues guard the secrets to poison-making carefully, lest magi start incorporating poison into their spells. Poisonbolt? Rain of Poison? Poison Elemental? Nobody wants that.

69605.name: Deadly Shot
69605.flavorText: Our ballista operator is effective, but not picky.

78324.name: Death Strike
78324.flavorText: A little embarrassing when used on large minions.

78644.name: Deathbringer Saurfang
78644.text: Taunt Deathrattle: Return this to your hand. It costs Health instead of Mana.
78644.flavorText: "In hindsight, maybe I should have let the Alliance have all the fun back at the Wrathgate."

66872.name: Deathwing the Destroyer
66872.text: Battlecry: Destroy all other minions. Discard a card for each destroyed.
66872.flavorText: "He’s Deathwing? That one's Deathwing? You're Deathwing!? I'm DEATHWING! ARE THERE ANY OTHER DEATHWINGS I SHOULD KNOW ABOUT?"

111461.name: Deathwing, Mad Aspect
111461.flavorText: Bite that one, bite that other one, claw this one, swallow that one whole....

69663.name: Defender of Argus
69663.flavorText: You wouldn’t think that Argus would need this much defending. But it does.

95688.name: Defile
95688.text: Deal 1 damage to all minions. If any die, cast this again.
95688.flavorText: This spell was originally designed to help warlocks clean up their hard drives.

115971.name: Demolition Renovator
115971.flavorText: "Look, the Sire said he wanted something more open concept..."

111458.name: Demonic Studies
111458.text: Discover a Demon. Your next one costs (1) less.
111458.flavorText: "Do you wanna summon a demon? I wanna summon a demon!"

69668.name: Dire Wolf Alpha
69668.flavorText: We are pretty excited about the upcoming release of Dire Wolf Beta, just repost this sign for a chance at a key.

102225.name: Dirty Rat
102225.text: Taunt Battlecry: Your opponent summons a random minion from their hand.
102225.flavorText: It's not his fault… Someone keeps stealing his soap!

111457.name: Doomguard
111457.flavorText: Summoning a doomguard is risky. Someone is going to die.

76317.name: Doomsayer
76317.text: At the start of your turn, destroy ALL minions.
76317.flavorText: He's almost been right so many times. He was sure it was coming during the Cataclysm.

102191.name: Dragonbane
102191.text: After you use your Hero Power, deal 5 damage to a random enemy.
102191.flavorText: *Thunk* "That wasn’t a dragon!" *Thunk* "THAT wasn’t a dragon!"

69735.name: Drain Soul
69735.flavorText: Cleans even the toughest clogs with just a flick of the wrist!

102230.name: Dread Corsair
102230.text: Taunt Costs (1) less per Attack of your weapon.
102230.flavorText: "Yarrrr" is a pirate word that means "Greetings, milord."

69595.name: Druid of the Claw
69595.text: Choose One - Transform into a 7/6 with Rush; or a 4/9 with Taunt.
69595.flavorText: Cat or Bear? Cat or Bear?! I just cannot CHOOSE!

69565.name: Elven Archer
69565.flavorText: Don't bother asking her out on a date. She'll shoot you down.

97344.name: Elven Minstrel
97344.flavorText: "After that gig in Hamlin went south, I swore off rats."

97346.name: Enhanced Dreadlord
97346.flavorText: Photo actually taken across the street in the reflection of a doorknob.

69614.name: Equality
69614.text: Change the Health of ALL minions to 1.
69614.flavorText: We are all special unique snowflakes... with 1 Health.

112925.name: Evasive Wyrm
112925.flavorText: Deftly dodges spells like a real wiggle wyrm.

102205.name: Eviscerate
102205.flavorText: There is a high cost to Eviscerating your opponent. You might tweak your elbow! That really hurts!

111350.name: Expendable Performers
111350.text: Summon seven 1/1 Illidari with Rush. If they all die this turn, summon seven more.
111350.flavorText: When someone gets injured, it's considered performance art.

86235.name: Explosive Runes
86235.text: Secret: After your opponent plays a minion, deal 6 damage to it and any excess to their hero.
86235.flavorText: Sometimes it's safer NOT to read the warning signs.

69603.name: Explosive Trap
69603.text: Secret: When your hero is attacked, deal 2 damage to all enemies.
69603.flavorText: It traps your food AND cooks it for you!

69740.name: Eye Beam
69740.text: Lifesteal. Deal 3 damage to a minion. Outcast: This costs (1).

76329.name: Faerie Dragon
76329.flavorText: Adorable. Immune to Magic. Doesn't pee on the rug. The perfect pet!

111379.name: Fal'dorei Strider
111379.text: Battlecry: Shuffle 3 Ambushes into your deck. When drawn, summon a 4/4 Spider.
111379.flavorText: What’s worse? Seeing the spider, or NOT seeing the spider, but knowing it’s somewhere in your deck?

102745.name: Fan of Knives
102745.text: Deal 1 damage to all enemy minions. Draw a card.
102745.flavorText: I wouldn't say I LOVE knives, but I'm definitely a fan.

76293.name: Far Sight
76293.text: Draw a card. That card costs (3) less.
76293.flavorText: Drek'thar can't see, but he can see. You know what I mean? It's ok if you don't.

69688.name: Feral Rage
69688.text: Choose One - Give your hero +4 Attack this turn; or Gain 8 Armor.
69688.flavorText: Let's be honest. One option is a lot ragier than the other.

69626.name: Feral Spirit
69626.flavorText: Spirit wolves are like regular wolves with pom-poms.

69534.name: Fiery War Axe
69534.flavorText: During times of tranquility and harmony, this weapon was called by its less popular name, Chilly Peace Axe.

69516.name: Fire Elemental
69516.flavorText: He can never take a bath. Ewww.

111469.name: Fire Fly
111469.text: Battlecry: Add a 1/2 Elemental to your hand.
111469.flavorText: Archnemeses: small children with glass jars.

69501.name: Fireball
69501.flavorText: This spell is useful for burning things. If you're looking for spells that toast things, or just warm them a little, you're in the wrong place.

97375.name: Firelands Portal
97375.text: Deal 6 damage. Summon a random 6-Cost minion.
97375.flavorText: Come to beautiful Firelands! Where it's "Way nicer than the Abyssal Maw!"

102194.name: Flame Geyser
102194.text: Deal 2 damage. Add a 1/2 Elemental to your hand.

69636.name: Flame Imp
69636.flavorText: Imps like being on fire. They just do.

69502.name: Flamestrike
69502.text: Deal 5 damage to all enemy minions.
69502.flavorText: When the ground is on fire, you should not stop, drop, and roll.

76294.name: Flametongue Totem
76294.flavorText: Totemsmiths like to use the rarest woods for their totems. There are even rumors of totems made of Ironbark Protectors.

111375.name: Flik Skyshiv
111375.text: Battlecry: Destroy a minion and all copies of it (wherever they are).
111375.flavorText: Junior explorers scan the night sky in fear of her candle’s flame!

66854.name: Fogsail Freebooter
66854.text: Battlecry: If you have a weapon equipped, deal 2 damage.
66854.flavorText: Goes cheap on wardrobe so he can spend on weaponry.

69604.name: Freezing Trap
69604.text: Secret: When an enemy minion attacks, return it to its owner's hand. It costs (2) more.
69604.flavorText: "Dang, that's cold." - appropriate response to Freezing Trap, or a mean joke.

102719.name: Frightened Flunky
102719.flavorText: Some people just aren't cut out to be supervillain material.

78325.name: Frost Strike
78325.text: Deal 3 damage to a minion. If that kills it, Discover a Frost Rune card.
78325.flavorText: Anyone up for some frost bowling?

111365.name: Frostbolt
111365.text: Deal 3 damage to a character and Freeze it.
111365.flavorText: It is customary to yell "Chill out!" or "Freeze!" or "Ice ice, baby!" when you play this card.

111316.name: Frostmourne
111316.text: Deathrattle: Summon every minion killed by this weapon.
111316.flavorText: Death Nights, Frost Morn, what's next - Blood Noon?

111326.name: Frostwyrm's Fury
111326.text: Deal 5 damage. Freeze all enemy minions. Summon a 5/5 Frostwyrm.
111326.flavorText: Terrible destruction, but minty fresh breath!

69645.name: Frothing Berserker
69645.text: Whenever a minion takes damage, gain +1 Attack.
69645.flavorText: He used to work as an accountant before he tried his hand at Berserkering.

64465.name: Gan'arg Glaivesmith
64465.text: Outcast: Give your hero +3 Attack this turn.

80819.name: Gnome Muncher
80819.text: Taunt, Lifesteal At the end of your turn, attack the lowest Health enemy.

112097.name: Gnomelia, S.A.F.E. Pilot
112097.text: Rush. Also damages minions next to whomever this attacks. Deathrattle: Deal 2 damage to all enemies.

86548.name: Gorillabot A-3
86548.text: Battlecry: If you control another Mech, Discover a Mech.
86548.flavorText: A-1 and A-2 went nuts, when they should have gone bolts.

80645.name: Grave Strength
80645.text: Give your minions +1 Attack. Spend 5 Corpses to give them +3 instead.

111353.name: Greybough
111353.text: Taunt Deathrattle: Give a random friendly minion "Deathrattle: Summon Greybough."
111353.flavorText: The best time to plant a tree was 20 years ago. The next best time is when you lose a minion.

102196.name: Grimestreet Outfitter
102196.text: Battlecry: Give all minions in your hand +1/+1.
102196.flavorText: If you bargain hard, he'll throw in the hat.

69643.name: Grommash Hellscream
69643.flavorText: Grommash drank the tainted blood of Mannoroth, dooming the orcs to green skin and red eyes! Maybe not his best decision.

102790.name: Hammer of Wrath
102790.flavorText: A good paladin has many tools. Hammer of Wrath, Pliers of Vengeance, Hacksaw of Justice, etc.

111370.name: Hammer of the Naaru
111370.flavorText: The naaru wasn't using it. It doesn't have arms.

102197.name: Hand of A'dal
102197.text: Give a minion +2/+1. Draw a card.
102197.flavorText: When it meets the Hand of Gul'dan, they're SHAKING.

97333.name: Heavy Plate
97333.flavorText: "You asked for unbendable, unwavering armor–I don't see why you're upset."

69519.name: Hellfire
69519.flavorText: It's spells like these that make it hard for Warlocks to get decent help.

111320.name: Hematurge
111320.text: Battlecry: Spend a Corpse to Discover a Blood Rune card.
111320.flavorText: She's here to PUMP! YOU UP!

86540.name: Hench-Clan Burglar
86540.flavorText: She’s more of a rat burglar.

97343.name: Hench-Clan Thug
97343.text: After your hero attacks, give this minion +1/+1.
97343.flavorText: Hard time making ends meet? Hate the League of Explorers? Get a job henching!

69551.name: Hex
69551.text: Transform a minion into a 0/1 Frog with Taunt.
69551.flavorText: If you Hex a Murloc... it really isn't much of a change, is it?

69508.name: Holy Nova
69508.text: Deal 2 damage to all enemy minions. Restore 2 Health to all friendly characters.
69508.flavorText: If the Holy Light forsakes you, good luck casting this spell. Also, you're probably a jerk.

69509.name: Holy Smite
69509.flavorText: It doesn't matter how pious you are. Everyone needs a good smiting now and again.

111325.name: Horn of Winter
111325.flavorText: Much better than the Horn of Loseter.

69608.name: Ice Barrier
69608.text: Secret: When your hero is attacked, gain 8 Armor.
69608.flavorText: This is Rank 1. Rank 2 is Chocolate Milk Barrier.

111362.name: Ice Trap
111362.text: Secret: When your opponent casts a spell, return it to their hand instead. It costs (1) more.
111362.flavorText: I literally watched the Hunter place it down in front of me and I still stepped in it.

66176.name: Illidari Inquisitor
66176.text: Rush. After your hero attacks an enemy, this attacks it too.
66176.flavorText: Armed with fear, big eyes, ruthless efficiency, almost fanatical devotion to your hero, and nice brown robes.

97377.name: Illidari Studies
97377.text: Discover an Outcast card. Your next one costs (1) less.

97379.name: Immolation Aura
97379.text: Deal 1 damage to all minions twice.
97379.flavorText: If you can't take the heat, stop standing in the fire.

69550.name: Innervate
69550.text: Gain 1 Mana Crystal this turn only.
69550.flavorText: Some druids still have flashbacks from strangers yelling "Innervate me!!" at them.

97376.name: Jeweled Macaw
97376.text: Battlecry: Add a random Beast to your hand.
97376.flavorText: It’s not LITERALLY jeweled. The goblins were terribly disappointed.

111468.name: Justicar Trueheart
111468.text: Battlecry: Replace your starting Hero Power with a better one.
111468.flavorText: It's like putting racing stripes and a giant spoiler on your hero power.

76271.name: Kalecgos
76271.text: Your first spell each turn costs (0). Battlecry: Discover a spell.
76271.flavorText: He was once the Aspect of Magic but gave it up to focus on cheap tricks.

111381.name: Kalimos, Primal Lord
111381.text: Battlecry: If you played an Elemental last turn, cast an Elemental Invocation.
111381.flavorText: All that's missing is a little heart.

102184.name: Kayn Sunfury
102184.flavorText: "Armor and heals may slow my zeal, but fel and glaives excite me!"

111361.name: Kill Command
111361.text: Deal 3 damage. If you control a Beast, deal 5 damage instead.

69539.name: Kobold Geomancer
69539.flavorText: In the old days, Kobolds were the finest candle merchants in the land. Then they got pushed too far...

111368.name: Lady Liadrin
111368.text: Battlecry: Add a copy of each spell you cast on friendly characters this game to your hand.
111368.flavorText: When it comes to spells, she loves 'em then she librams.

111462.name: Leeroy Jenkins
111462.text: Charge. Battlecry: Summon two 1/1 Whelps for your opponent.
111462.flavorText: At least he has Angry Chicken.

111453.name: Lesser Amethyst Spellstone
111453.text: Lifesteal. Deal 3 damage to a minion. (Take damage from your cards to upgrade.)
111453.flavorText: A purple stone Azari carved For dark hearts, craving, power-starved. The first to bow, the warlock Rin, Embraced the darkness, slew her kin.

111371.name: Lesser Diamond Spellstone
111371.text: Resurrect 2 different friendly minions. (Cast 4 spells to upgrade.)
111371.flavorText: A diamond, white, this stone the eighth A precious jewel for those of faith A whispered prayer restores the lost But none among them know the cost.

111360.name: Lesser Emerald Spellstone
111360.text: Summon two 3/3 Wolves. (Play a Secret to upgrade.)
111360.flavorText: An emerald stone for Tauren hands Who sought its strength to save their lands Their tribes now lost, their rage released Who’s hunting now? And who’s the beast?

111352.name: Lesser Jasper Spellstone
111352.text: Deal 2 damage to a minion. (Gain 3 Armor to upgrade.)
111352.flavorText: In ancient woods, elves fought the curse The demon’s shadow to disperse But hatred raged and frail souls turned Now horned and hooved their forests burned.

76320.name: Lifedrinker
76320.text: Battlecry: Deal 3 damage to the enemy hero. Restore 3 Health to your hero.
76320.flavorText: In a pinch, he'll also settle for Holy Water: Zero.

86534.name: Lightbomb
86534.text: Deal damage to each minion equal to its Attack.
86534.flavorText: This is what happens when you allow goblins to be priests.

69625.name: Lightning Bolt
69625.flavorText: Lightning Bolt! Lightning Bolt! Lightning Bolt!

69629.name: Lightning Storm
69629.text: Deal 3 damage to all enemy minions. Overload: (1)
69629.flavorText: An umbrella won't be effective, I'm afraid.

76289.name: Living Roots
76289.text: Choose One - Deal 2 damage; or Summon two 1/1 Saplings.
76289.flavorText: 2 out of 2 saplings recommend that you summon the saplings.

69637.name: Lord Jaraxxus
69637.flavorText: "TRIFLING GNOME! YOUR ARROGANCE WILL BE YOUR UNDOING!!!!"

69662.name: Mad Bomber
69662.text: Battlecry: Deal 3 damage randomly split between all other characters.
69662.flavorText: He's not really all that crazy, he is just not as careful with explosives as he should be.

111374.name: Madame Lazul
111374.text: Battlecry: Discover a copy of a card in your opponent's hand.
111374.flavorText: Of course she knows the future, she’s been looking at your cards the WHOLE TIME!

66869.name: Malygos the Spellweaver
66869.text: Battlecry: Draw spells until your hand is full.
66869.flavorText: After many years, Malygos has decided mortals can use magic. ALL THE MAGIC!

97608.name: Mana Geode
97608.flavorText: Gadgetzan, where even the pet rocks have pet rocks.

69511.name: Mark of the Wild
69511.text: Give a minion Taunt and +2/+3. (+2 Attack/+3 Health)
69511.flavorText: Not to be confused with Jim of the Wild.

111323.name: Marrow Manipulator
111323.text: Battlecry: Spend up to 5 Corpses. Deal 2 damage to a random enemy for each.

111358.name: Master's Call
111358.text: Discover a minion in your deck. If all 3 are Beasts, draw them all.

69731.name: Menacing Nimbus
69731.text: Battlecry: Add a random Elemental to your hand.
69731.flavorText: Electra stores her elementals in the cloud.

76308.name: Metamorphosis
76308.text: Swap your Hero Power to "Deal 5 damage." After 2 uses, swap it back.
76308.flavorText: As the humble caterpillar becomes a beautiful butterfly, so too does a demon hunter become a hideous mass of writhing destruction and unfettered chaos.

111324.name: Might of Menethil
111324.text: Battlecry: Spend up to 3 Corpses. Freeze that many enemy minions.
111324.flavorText: Menethil's Might, at night, fights the light, not quite the blight, right?

111473.name: Mind Control Tech
111473.text: Battlecry: If your opponent has 4 or more minions, take control of one.
111473.flavorText: Mind Control technology is getting better, but that's not saying much.

111472.name: Molten Giant
111472.text: Costs (1) less for each Health your hero is missing.
111472.flavorText: He gets terrible heartburn. BECAUSE HE IS FULL OF LAVA.

69553.name: Mortal Coil
69553.text: Deal 1 damage to a minion. If that kills it, draw a card.
69553.flavorText: If your spells look like horrifying skulls, let's be honest, you should get to draw some cards.

111470.name: Mountain Giant
111470.text: Costs (1) less for each other card in your hand.
111470.flavorText: His mother said that he was just big boned.

111382.name: Muck Pools
111382.text: Transform a friendly minion into one that costs (1) more.
111382.flavorText: Making a dredger is easier than you'd think. You don't need to worry about mucking it up!

69675.name: Murloc Tidecaller
69675.text: Whenever you summon a Murloc, gain +1 Attack.
69675.flavorText: This guy gets crazy strong at family reunions.

76270.name: Murloc Warleader
76270.flavorText: Do Murlocs ever get tired of making the same old sound? Nope! Mrglglrglglglglglglgl!

102228.name: Murmy
102228.flavorText: Unlike other mummies, they rolled him up with rice, sliced cucumbers, and soy sauce on the side.

96916.name: Muster for Battle
96916.text: Summon three 1/1 Silver Hand Recruits. Equip a 1/4 Weapon.
96916.flavorText: "I'm bringing the guacamole!" – One of the most successful (yet rare) Silver Hand rallying cries

111328.name: Necrotic Mortician
111328.text: Battlecry: If a friendly Undead died after your last turn, Discover an Unholy Rune card.
111328.flavorText: Her hair, just like her name, is full of 'tic's.

69713.name: Nerubian Egg
69713.flavorText: Eggs are a good source of protein and Nerubians.

111319.name: Nerubian Swarmguard
111319.text: Taunt Battlecry: Summon two copies of this minion.
111319.flavorText: How long can this go on? Apparently even in death.

112098.name: Night Elf Huntress
112098.text: Battlecry: Deal 3 damage to three different enemies. (You pick the targets!)
112098.flavorText: A triple threat, all on her own.

62442.name: Novice Zapper
62442.flavorText: The novices would prefer that he did not.

78641.name: Noxious Cadaver
78641.text: Battlecry: Deal 2 damage to an enemy and your hero.
78641.flavorText: Shouldn't have eaten that gas station sushi.

66870.name: Nozdormu the Eternal
66870.text: Start of Game: If this is in BOTH players' decks, turns are only 15 seconds long.
66870.flavorText: Live life in the fast lane. As long as your opponent does too.

111355.name: Oaken Summons
111355.text: Gain 6 Armor. Summon a minion from your deck that costs (4) or less.
111355.flavorText: The Guild used oak trees until they all turned to ash.

95732.name: Obsidian Statue
95732.text: Taunt, Lifesteal Deathrattle: Destroy a random enemy minion.
95732.flavorText: The original artist spent many hours with a fine chisel perfecting the facial expression for maximum tauntiness.

66866.name: Onyxia the Broodmother
66866.text: At the end of each turn, fill your board with 1/1 Whelps.
66866.flavorText: Throw more dots, throw more dots, more dots, more dots!

102207.name: Overdraft
102207.text: Tradeable Unlock your Overloaded Mana Crystals to deal that much damage.
102207.flavorText: Wait. It costs mana to be out of mana?!

66858.name: Overlord Runthak
66858.text: Rush. Whenever this attacks, give +1/+1 to all minions in your hand.
66858.flavorText: Knows how to lift everyone up while tearing every enemy down.

111356.name: Park Panther
111356.text: Rush. Whenever this attacks, give your hero +3 Attack this turn.
111356.flavorText: Somebody called animal control once. It didn't work out very well for anybody.

78335.name: Plagued Grain
78335.text: Gain 4 Corpses. Shuffle four Crates into your deck that summon a 2/2 Undead when drawn.
78335.flavorText: Oh, don’t mind the smell. They're just aged!

76323.name: Plated Beetle
76323.flavorText: "Ok, your party has defeated the beetle." "I put it on my head." "What?" "I put it on my head. Like a hat."

69593.name: Power of the Wild
69593.text: Choose One - Give your minions +1/+1; or Summon a 3/2 Panther.
69593.flavorText: Never look a panther in the eye. Or is it 'Always look a panther in the eye'? Well, it's one of those.

69623.name: Preparation
69623.text: The next spell you cast this turn costs (2) less.

76327.name: Primordial Drake
76327.text: Taunt Battlecry: Deal 2 damage to all other minions.
76327.flavorText: Before he became a rap artist.

111366.name: Primordial Glyph
111366.text: Discover a spell. Reduce its Cost by (2).
111366.flavorText: It's the Ancient Tol'vir symbol for "Whoops!"

111689.name: Prince Renathal
111689.text: Your deck size and starting Health are 40.
111689.flavorText: A lot of kids go through a rebellious phase, but Prince Renathal's was a bit extreme.

69566.name: Psychic Conjurer
69566.text: Battlecry: Copy a card in your opponent’s deck and add it to your hand.
69566.flavorText: "I see... a WISP? Why do you have a wisp?!"

69691.name: Quick Shot
69691.text: Deal 3 damage. If your hand is empty, draw a card.

69588.name: Raging Felscreamer
69588.text: Battlecry: The next Demon you play costs (2) less.
69588.flavorText: Screaming loudly will not reduce the cost of non-demonic goods.

102272.name: Ragnaros the Firelord
102272.text: Can't attack. At the end of your turn, deal 8 damage to a random enemy.
102272.flavorText: Ragnaros was summoned by the Dark Iron dwarves, who were eventually enslaved by the Firelord. Summoning Ragnaros often doesn’t work out the way you want it to.

111377.name: Raiding Party
111377.text: Draw 2 Pirates from your deck. Combo: And a weapon.
111377.flavorText: And a bowl of chips. And some of those little cocktail weenies!

111363.name: Rat Trap
111363.text: Secret: After your opponent plays three cards in a turn, summon a 6/6 Rat.
111363.flavorText: MISSING: One giant rat. Please return to King Togwaggle.

113109.name: Raven Idol
113109.text: Choose One - Discover a minion; or Discover a spell.
113109.flavorText: Was petrified when it found out it didn't make the cut for Azerothian Idol.

72250.name: Redgill Razorjaw
72250.flavorText: One fish, two fish, red fish replaces blue fish.

80648.name: Remorseless Winter
80648.text: Deal 2 damage to all enemies. Draw a card.
80648.flavorText: In the Badlands, this is a Rare.

102969.name: Replicating Menace
102969.flavorText: It's a car! *Whomp whomp whomp* It's a robot! *Whomp whom-CRUNCH* It's… three.. smaller robots!

98053.name: Resistance Aura
98053.text: Your opponent's spells cost (1) more. Lasts enemy turns.
98053.flavorText: Perfect for defending against Beasts. Specifically small ones. Like, a very specific species of small insectoid animal. Ants. It resists ants.

69705.name: Righteous Protector
69705.flavorText: Original name was Tubular Protector, but this seems more bodacious.

102222.name: Royal Librarian
102222.flavorText: Books on how to flip the Auction House are down that way.

69621.name: SI:7 Agent
69621.flavorText: The agents of SI:7 are responsible for Stormwind's covert activities. Their duties include espionage, assassination, and throwing surprise birthday parties for the royal family.

111459.name: Sanguine Depths
111459.text: Deal 1 damage to a minion and give it +2 Attack.
111459.flavorText: There may not be any skeletons in the closets at Castle Nathria, but there sure are souls in the basement.

111378.name: Sap
111378.text: Return an enemy minion to your opponent's hand.

69600.name: Savannah Highmane
69600.flavorText: In the jungle, the mighty jungle, the lion gets slowly consumed by hyenas.

76322.name: Sea Giant
76322.text: Costs (1) less for each other minion on the battlefield.

69542.name: Sen'jin Shieldmasta
69542.flavorText: Sen'jin Village is nice, if you like trolls and dust.

95746.name: Shadow Ascendant
95746.text: At the end of your turn, give another random friendly minion +1/+1.
95746.flavorText: When you're at the bottom, there's nowhere to ascend, but up.

111372.name: Shadow Word: Pain
111372.text: Destroy a minion with 3 or less Attack.
111372.flavorText: A step up from a spell cast by many beginning acolytes: "Shadow Word: Annoy".

69616.name: Shadow Word: Ruin
69616.text: Destroy all minions with 5 or more Attack.
69616.flavorText: Discovered by a worgen priest after a giant spilled a drink on her new white robes.

69622.name: Shadowstep
69622.text: Return a friendly minion to your hand. It costs (2) less.
69622.flavorText: Rogue dance troops will sometimes Shadowstep away at the end of a performance. Crowds love it.

76302.name: Shield Block
76302.flavorText: Shields were invented because Face Block is USELESS.

69641.name: Shield Slam
69641.text: Deal 1 damage to a minion for each Armor you have.
69641.flavorText: "What is a better weapon? The sharp one your enemies expect, or the blunt one they ignore?" - The Art of Warrior, Chapter 9

113116.name: Ship's Chirurgeon
113116.text: After you summon a minion, give it +1 Health.
113116.flavorText: Knows the answer to every medical question except how to pronounce his name.

69698.name: Shooting Star
69698.text: Deal 1 damage to a minion and the minions next to it.

111367.name: Silvermoon Portal
111367.text: Give a minion +2/+2. Summon a random 2-Cost minion.
111367.flavorText: What's Millhouse Manastorm doing in Silvermoon?

69634.name: Siphon Soul
69634.text: Destroy a minion. Restore 3 Health to your hero.
69634.flavorText: You probably should avoid siphoning your own soul. You might create some kind of weird infinite loop.

86190.name: Skeletal Sidekick
86190.flavorText: He's got your back. And your arm.

69638.name: Slam
69638.text: Deal 2 damage to a minion. If it survives, draw a card.
69638.flavorText: "Dun da dun, dun da dun": if you've heard an ogre sing this, it's too late.

69726.name: Sleepy Dragon
69726.flavorText: Local villagers call her "Naps Under the Mountain."

95755.name: Snowflipper Penguin
95755.flavorText: On land, a group of penguins is called a "waddle."

111332.name: Soulbreaker
111332.text: After your hero attacks and kills a minion, gain 2 Corpses.

111322.name: Soulstealer
111322.text: Battlecry: Destroy all other minions. Gain 1 Corpse for each enemy destroyed.
111322.flavorText: "Wanna see what destruction looks like? Here it is in undead form - it's your boy Soulstealer!"

69679.name: Southsea Captain
69679.flavorText: When he saves enough plunder, he's going to commission an enormous captain's hat. He has hat envy.

113225.name: Southsea Deckhand
113225.text: Has Charge while you have a weapon equipped.
113225.flavorText: Pirates are into this new fad called "Planking".

111376.name: Spectral Cutlass
111376.text: Lifesteal Whenever you play a card from another class, gain +1 Durability.
111376.flavorText: So sharp it can cut through a spectral tomato!

69684.name: Spectral Sight
69684.flavorText: "Pick a card, any card! Preferably the left- or right-most card."

111369.name: Spikeridged Steed
111369.text: Give a minion +2/+6 and Taunt. When it dies, summon a Stegodon.

102212.name: Spirit Bomb
102212.text: Deal 4 damage to a minion and your hero.
102212.flavorText: Might take a few episodes to power up.

111380.name: Spirit Claws
111380.text: Has +2 Attack while you have Spell Damage.
111380.flavorText: They'll be MUCH easier to use once they add the spiritthumb.

69706.name: Stand Against Darkness
69706.flavorText: Or if you're too tired, you can just kind of lean against the darkness.

102195.name: Stargazer Luna
102195.text: After you play the right-most card in your hand, draw a card.

82072.name: Stitched Giant
82072.text: Costs (1) less for each Corpse you've spent this game.

112923.name: Stonehill Defender
112923.flavorText: Briefly tried stand-up comedy under the name "Stonehill Offender", but turtles are just too thin-skinned.

69544.name: Stormwind Champion
69544.flavorText: When Deathwing assaulted the capital, this soldier was the only member of his squad to survive. Now he's all bitter and stuff.

69658.name: Stranglethorn Tiger
69658.flavorText: The wonderful thing about tigers is tigers are wonderful things!

69742.name: Swashburglar
69742.text: Battlecry: Add a random card from another class to your hand.

111351.name: Swipe
111351.text: Deal 4 damage to an enemy and 1 damage to all other enemies.
111351.flavorText: When a bear rears back and extends his arms, he's about to Swipe! ... or hug.

111463.name: Sylvanas Windrunner
111463.text: Deathrattle: Take control of a random enemy minion.
111463.flavorText: Sylvanas was turned into the Banshee Queen by Arthas, but he probably should have just killed her because it just pissed her off.

66856.name: Taelan Fordring
66856.text: Taunt, Divine Shield Deathrattle: Draw your highest Cost minion.
66856.flavorText: After growing up with the Scarlet Crusade for most of his life, Taelan finally realized they were maybe not the nicest people.

76319.name: Tar Creeper
76319.text: Taunt Has +2 Attack during your opponent's turn.
76319.flavorText: If you won't come to the tar pits, we'll bring them to you!

86539.name: Tess Greymane
86539.text: Battlecry: Replay every card from another class you've played this game (targets chosen randomly).
86539.flavorText: Those who cannot remember their card history are doomed to repeat it.

86731.name: Thassarian
86731.text: Reborn Battlecry and Deathrattle: Deal 2 damage to a random enemy.
86731.flavorText: A natural born leader. And an unnatural reborn leader.

111329.name: The Scourge
111329.text: Fill your board with random Undead.
111329.flavorText: “You speak of justice? Of cowardice? I will show you the justice of the grave and the true meaning of fear.”

111354.name: Thickhide Kodo
111354.flavorText: The introduction of professions was devastating for kodo populations.

102209.name: Thing from Below
102209.text: Taunt Costs (1) less for each Totem you've summoned this game.
102209.flavorText: Just can't resist the opportunity to hang around with a bunch of totems.

66861.name: Thrive in the Shadows
66861.flavorText: Why would your spells be afraid of the dark? It's easier to nap there.

69613.name: Tirion Fordring
69613.flavorText: If you haven't heard the Tirion Fordring theme song, it's because it doesn't exist.

111460.name: Town Crier
111460.text: Battlecry: Draw a Rush minion from your deck.
111460.flavorText: When he was younger, he was the town crybaby.

69545.name: Tracking
69545.flavorText: For the person who just cannot decide what card to put into a deck!

76325.name: Twilight Drake
76325.text: Battlecry: Gain +1 Health for each card in your hand.
76325.flavorText: Twilight drakes feed on Mystical Energy. And Tacos.

69635.name: Twisting Nether
69635.flavorText: The Twisting Nether is a formless place of magic and illusion and destroyed minions.

111349.name: Umberwing
111349.flavorText: Demon Hunters refer to these glaives as "the ol’ flappy-attackys."

111327.name: Vampiric Blood
111327.text: Give your hero +5 Health. Spend 3 Corpses to gain 5 more and draw a card.

113111.name: Vicious Slitherspear
113111.text: After you cast a spell, gain +1 Attack until your next turn.
113111.flavorText: He goes by ‘Fun-Loving Slitherspear’ on his dating profile.

76281.name: Voidwalker
76281.flavorText: No relation to "The Voidsteppers", the popular Void-based dance troupe.

69547.name: Voodoo Doctor
69547.flavorText: Voodoo is an oft-misunderstood art. But it is art.

86551.name: Vulpera Scoundrel
86551.text: Battlecry: Discover a spell or pick a mystery choice.
86551.flavorText: A spell is a spell, but the mystery choice could be anything! (It's also a spell.)

111471.name: Wandmaker
111471.text: Battlecry: Add a 1-Cost spell from your class to your hand.
111471.flavorText: She creates incredibly affordable wands of all shapes and sizes. But not owls. The owl is all-natural.

102218.name: Wargear
102218.flavorText: WAR! GEAR! What is it good for?

69703.name: Warhorse Trainer
69703.text: Your Silver Hand Recruits have +2 Attack and Taunt.
69703.flavorText: He doesn't even get Sundays off. Every day he's hostling.

112100.name: Warsong Grunt
112100.text: Rush. After this attacks and kills a minion, it may attack again.
112100.flavorText: Where do you think the chickens learned to be angry?

111348.name: Wayward Sage
111348.text: Outcast: Reduce the Cost of the left and right-most cards in your hand by (1).
111348.flavorText: Carry on my wayward sage. There'll be peace and no more rage.

69556.name: Whirlwind
69556.flavorText: The way to tell seasoned warriors from novice ones: the novices yell "wheeeee" while whirlwinding.

76321.name: Wild Pyromancer
76321.text: After you cast a spell, deal 1 damage to ALL minions.
76321.flavorText: BOOM BABY BOOM! BAD IS GOOD! DOWN WITH GOVERNMENT!

102188.name: Witchwood Apple
102188.text: Add two 2/2 Treants to your hand.
102188.flavorText: An apple a day keeps the worgen at bay.

69654.name: Worgen Infiltrator
69654.flavorText: If you want to stop a worgen from infiltrating, just yell, "No! Bad boy!"

76288.name: Wrath
76288.text: Choose One - Deal 3 damage to a minion; or 1 damage and draw a card.
76288.flavorText: The talk around the Ratchet Inn is that this card is too good and should be a Legendary.

69660.name: Youthful Brewmaster
69660.text: Battlecry: Return a friendly minion from the battlefield to your hand.
69660.flavorText: His youthful enthusiasm doesn’t always equal excellence in his brews. Don’t drink the Mogu Stout!

111465.name: Ysera
111465.text: At the end of your turn, get two random Dream cards.
111465.flavorText: Ysera rules the Emerald Dream. Which is some kind of green-mirror-version of the real world, or something?

76310.name: Zola the Gorgon
76310.text: Battlecry: Choose a friendly minion. Add a Golden copy of it to your hand.
76310.flavorText: Her name seems a bit cheesy.
